  "text": "This paper complements a series of articles about the April 2007 synchronous observations of the Galactic Center from radio to γ-rays [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). Here, we have recapped the results on the brightest flare ever detected simultaneously at NIR and X-ray frequencies. We have also reported for the first time γ-ray constraints on such an event, which, added to our MIR/NIR/X-ray spectral measurements, constitute the broadest simulaneous spectrum of a flare ever achieved. The essential observational conclusions may be summarized as follows:",
